Stop to Suppression of Koreans in Japan Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 18 (KCNA) -- The press headquarters of the South Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration reportedly made public a statement on Feb. 13 urging the Japanese public security authorities and ultra right forces to immediately stop the violation of the rights of Koreans in Japan and the political suppression of them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement referred to the fact that the Japanese police authorities mobilized a lot of armed policemen on Feb. 6 to search the office of the Hyogo Prefectural Headquarters of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and other Chongryon-related facilities and walked away the chief of the Business Office of the Hyogo Prefectural Commercial Association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said actions committed by the Japanese ultra-right forces against Koreans in Japan are a wanton violation of Chongryon's rights and political crackdown upon it, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koreans in Japan were compelled to live in a foreign land entirely because the Japanese reactionaries forcibly drafted a large number of Koreans in a bid to force them to do slave labor at their coal mines and munitions factories when Korea was under Japan's military occupation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 The Japanese reactionaries look down upon and suppress Koreans in Japan instead of making an apology for the past crimes. This is the height of impudence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will never remain an onlooker to these outrages of the Japanese ultra-right forces.
